title: Soil moisture variations
description: Create a contour plot to analyze the variations in soil moisture across different agricultural fields, using a gradient from 'wheat' for dry areas to 'darkgreen' for wet areas.
solution:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import plotly.express as px

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
contour = plt.contourf(x, y, a, cmap='RdYlGn', levels=10)
cbar = plt.colorbar(contour)
cbar.set_label('Soil Moisture Level')
plt.contourf(x, y, a, levels=[-100, -75, -50, -25, 0, 25, 50, 75, 100], colors=['wheat', 'navajowhite', 'lightgreen', 'yellowgreen', 'green', 'forestgreen', 'darkgreen'])

plt.title('Soil Moisture Variations Across Agricultural Fields')
plt.xlabel('X Coordinate')
plt.ylabel('Y Coordinate')
plt.show()
